<FIRST>r a PM-MercedesSeized     07-07 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Mercedes Seized,0197</SECOND>
<HEAD>State Grabs Brand New Mercedes In Lieu of Corporate Taxes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The state seized a 1989 Mercedes Benz sedan worth
$74,000 from a Mercedes executive's driveway, saying the automaker
owes Massachusetts about $7 million in corporate taxes.
   ``If Mercedes does not pay the state what it owes, we will go to
auction with the car to pay off a small portion of their bill,''
state Revenue Department spokeswoman Betsy Houghteling said Thursday
night.
   Mercedes executives could not be reached at their New Jersey
office after business hours and did not return a message left on
their answering machine.
   Authorities took possession of the Mercedes 560 SEL with garnet
paint and beige leather upholstery at the executive's home.
Houghteling declined to name the executive, because he personally
has done nothing wrong.
   ``It was a company car. That's why we took it,'' she said.
   On May 5, state Attorney General James Shannon won a default
judgment against Mercedes in Suffolk Superior Court for $6.9 million
in back taxes dating from 1982 to 1985, but Mercedes has refused to
pay.
   The manufacturer contends it isn't liable for the state taxes.
</TEXT>
