<FIRST>r i PM-Brazil-BusHijacking     07-07 0275</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Brazil-Bus Hijacking,0280</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Kill Escaped Cons Who Hijacked Bus in Brazil</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police today shot and killed three
escaped convicts and captured three others after the group tried to
rob a bank, then hijacked a bus and took a 12-year-old boy hostage,
officials said.
   The shootout ended a chase that began Thursday when the six men
tried to rob a branch of the Bahia State Bank in Uaua, in
northeastern Brazil, said the head of the Bahia State Security
Bureau, Carlos Anselmo.
   The men, armed with revolvers and a shotgun, had escaped from the
medium-security Lemos de Brito penitentiary, Anselmo said by
telephone from the state capital, Salvador.
   The men stopped a bus carrying about 40 passengers and ordered
the driver to head for Conceicao do Coite, a city of 60,000 people
200 miles away, Anselmo said.
   In Conceicao do Coite, scores of police surrounded the bus and
exchanged gunfire with the hijackers. Three passengers were slightly
injured, said a city official, Jackson Ferreira.
   Before dawn today, the hijackers took several hostages from the
bus and fled in a car provided by local authorities. Outside of
town, they released all the hostages except a 12-year-old boy, then
abandoned the car and fled on foot through the brush, Ferreira said.
   Police tracked the group to a remote cottage, surrounded it and
opened fire, killing three of the escapees and capturing the others,
Ferreira said. He said the hostage was released unharmed.
   ``This was a little paradise. There's never been anything like
this here before,'' said Ferreira. ``Today's a holiday for the
town's anniversary, but now the celebration is ruined.''
</TEXT>
