<FIRST>r a PM-GeneGotti     07-07 0191</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Gene Gotti,0197</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gene Gotti, Brother of Reputed Mob Boss, Gets Maximum for Drug Dealing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gene Gotti, brother of reputed Gambino mob boss
John Gotti, was sentenced today to 50 years in prison for running a
multimillion-dollar drug ring.
   U.S. District Judge John R. Bartels ignored defense lawyers'
appeals for mercy in handing down the maximum sentence.
   ``I have my obligations,'' he said.
   Codefendant John Carneglia was also given 50 years, and both
defendants were fined $75,000.
   Gotti, 42, and Carneglia, 44, were found guilty May 23 of being
at the center of a major heroin trafficking ring. Authorities
describe Gotti as a capo or captain in the Gambino crime family
reputedly headed by his brother and Carneglia as a soldier in the
organization.
   Defense lawyers said they were shocked at the severity of the
sentences, but said they were confident the convictions would be
overturned on appeal.
   Gotti and Carneglia stood silent and showed no emotion when
Bartels pronounced his sentence.
   Both have been in jail since June 29, a day after Bartels revoked
their bail, saying they continued to deal drugs after their
conviction.
</TEXT>
