<SECOND>AM-BRF--Sweden-Tanks,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Swedes Melt Down Soviet Tanks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A steel mill is melting down old Soviet
tanks to make car parts and steel pipes, a company spokesman said
Friday.
   ``It is good scrap metal, heavy and compact,'' said Verner
Riisager, an executive of Ovako Steel in Hofors, 120 miles north of
Stockholm.
   Ovako bought 2,000 tons of scrap metal from a company in
Leningrad, filling his junkyard with tank turrets, cannon barrels
and caterpillar treads, Riisager said.
   ``They had about 10,000 tons of scrapped tanks over there. I
guess the company and the fact that they could export was a result
of their perestroika,'' he said.
   Riisager was unable to say what model tank the company bought.
</TEXT>
