<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Scientists,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>International Federation Moves Meeting From Beijing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The International Astronautical Federation decided
Friday to move its annual congress in October from Beijing to
Malaga, Spain.
   The federation of 106 astronautical organizations from 38
countries said it ``has always tried to remain apart from the
domestic politics of member countries ... and to carry no judgments
on the internal affairs on any country.''
   The federation's executive committee said it took the action
because unidentified member countries had refused to attend the
meeting in Beijing.
   It expressed its gratitude to the Chinese Astronautical
Association for the preparatory work done for the congress and gave
an assurance that it would be allowed to organize another one soon.
   Beijing has been under martial law since May 20, declared amid a
pro-democracy movement that was crushed by the army June 3-4.
