<SECOND>PM-Regina Sale,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>Electrolux To Close Rahway Plant</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWARK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Electrolux Corp., days after completing its
purchase of troubled Regina Co., announced it is closing Regina's
production facility in Rahway and eliminating the positions of the
plant's 250 employees.
   Steve Cooper, Electrolux senior counsel, said Thursday the new
parent of the vacuum cleaner maker expects to phase out operations
in Rahway by Sept. 30.
   ``At that time, those employees will be out of a job,'' he said.
   The Marietta, Ga.-based company is negotiating severance packages
with local 411 of the International Union Of Electrical, Radio and
Machine Employees, which he said represents about 85 percent of the
Rahway employees, Cooper said.
   The Rahway closing leaves Regina with a lone plant in Long Beach,
Miss., employing about 1,000 employees. Cooper said the Rahway
workers are now on a two-week paid vacation and the Mississippi
plant is on an annual shutdown.
   Cooper said Regina will continue to make upright vacuum cleaners,
rug shampooers, its ``electric broom'' and a personal whirlpool bath
under the Regina name.
</TEXT>
